metadata.dc:description: We present a case of retropneumoperitoneum , pneumoperitoneum , pneumomediastinum and subcutaneous emphysema in a caquectic 17 years old young man with an important depressive disorder . Several possible etiopathogenic factors are discussed, as well as the pathways of transmission of the pulmonary , mediastinic and abdominal gas.
metadata.dc:title: A propósito de un caso de retroneumoperitoneo, neumoperitoneo, neumomediastino y enfisema subcutáneo idiopáticos.
[A case of idiopathic retropneumoperitoneum, pneumoperitoneum, pneumomediastinum and subcutaneous emphysema].
metadata.dc:publisher: Revista de medicina de la Universidad de Navarra
